article.headline: Texas-Tyler 76, New Orleans 52
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- An 11-0 run to start the second half helped New Orleans break open an 11-point halftime lead and take a 76-52 win over Texas-Tyler on Saturday. Shaun Reynolds, Bo McCalebb and James Parlow combined for 60 points as New Orleans (3-6) snapped a two-game losing skid. Reynolds had a game- and season-high 25 points, while McCalebb had 23 points and James Parlow added 12. The Privateers forced a season-high 27 turnovers. Anthony Reese paced Texas-Tyler (1-5) with 10 points. New Orleans shot 57 percent in the first half and got 12 points each from Reynolds and McCalebb to take a 39-28 halftime advantage. The Privateers never trailed in the game. Texas-Tyler hosted the Privateer men's and women's teams last fall in the aftermath of Hurricane Katrina. New Orleans played its fall semester home games at UT-Tyler's Patriot Center.
